Addresses feedback from PR #345 to eliminate repetitive null checks across multiple methods in `PostComposedSignalDiscretizer`.

## Changes

- **Added validation methods**:
  - `ensureDiscretizerInitialized()`: validates `discretizer` only
  - `ensureInitialized()`: validates both `discretizer` and `postMapper` (delegates to `ensureDiscretizerInitialized()`)

- **Refactored method validation**:
  - `mapInput()`, `constructAbstractAlphabet()`, `constructConcreteAlphabet()`: call `ensureDiscretizerInitialized()`
  - `mapOutput()`: calls `ensureInitialized()`

## Before/After

**Before:**
```java
@Override
public List<Double> mapInput(String s) {
    if (discretizer == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Discretizer has not been initialized...");
    }
    return discretizer.mapInput(s);
}

@Override
public String mapOutput(IOSignalPiece<List<Double>> concreteIO) {
    if (discretizer == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Discretizer has not been initialized...");
    }
    if (postMapper == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("PostMapper has not been initialized...");
    }
    // ...
}
```

**After:**
```java
@Override
public List<Double> mapInput(String s) {
    ensureDiscretizerInitialized();
    return discretizer.mapInput(s);
}

@Override
public String mapOutput(IOSignalPiece<List<Double>> concreteIO) {
    ensureInitialized();
    // ...
}

private void ensureDiscretizerInitialized() {
    if (discretizer == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Discretizer has not been initialized...");
    }
}

private void ensureInitialized() {
    ensureDiscretizerInitialized();
    if (postMapper == null) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("PostMapper has not been initialized...");
    }
}
```

