Standardizes format operation handling and simplifies word deletion logic in the editor operations layer.

## Changes

- **`src/editor/ops.ts`**: Restrict `FormatAction` type to `'toggle' | 'make' | 'unmake'` (was `'set' | 'unset'`)

- **`src/editor/applyToTiptap.ts`**: 
  - Replace `setBold()`/`unsetBold()` pattern with `editor.isActive()` + `toggleBold()` for all format operations
    - `'make'`: toggle only if not active
    - `'unmake'`: toggle only if active
  - Simplify `deleteLastWord` to check selection state: use `deleteSelection()` if selection exists, otherwise delete word

```typescript
// Before
if (action === 'set') {
  chain.setBold().run();
} else {
  chain.unsetBold().run();
}

// After
if (action === 'make') {
  if (!editor.isActive('bold')) {
    chain.toggleBold().run();
  }
} else {
  if (editor.isActive('bold')) {
    chain.toggleBold().run();
  }
}
```

