The refactor in PR #2 removed named exports from `backend/src/models/index.js`, breaking existing imports like `import { SolicitudVacaciones, Colaborador } from "../../models/index.js"` used throughout the codebase.

## Changes

- Re-export all 38 models as named exports from `backend/src/models/index.js`
- Use destructuring pattern to avoid name conflicts with imported model definition functions
- Maintain existing `models` object and `sequelize` exports

## Implementation

```javascript
// Destructure to avoid conflicts with imported function names
const {
  Aguinaldo: AguinaldoModel,
  Colaborador: ColaboradorModel,
  Estado: EstadoModel,
  // ... all 38 models
} = models;

// Re-export with original names
export {
  AguinaldoModel as Aguinaldo,
  ColaboradorModel as Colaborador,
  EstadoModel as Estado,
  // ... all 38 models
  sequelize,
};
```

This preserves backward compatibility without requiring changes to consumer code across seeds, controllers, and handlers.

