💬 We'd love your input! Share your thoughts on Copilot coding agent in our [2 minute survey](https://gh.io/copilot-coding-agent-survey).

`IGitExecutor.Execute` accepted a raw concatenated command string passed to `ProcessStartInfo.Arguments`, requiring manual quoting and breaking silently on values containing spaces or special characters.

## Changes

- **`IGitExecutor`** — signature changed from `Execute(string command, ...)` to `Execute(string[] args, ...)`
- **`GitExecutor`** — uses `ProcessStartInfo.ArgumentList` instead of `Arguments`; each argument is added individually with no OS-level parsing
- **`GitService`** — all ~30 call sites updated to pass typed arrays; manual quoting eliminated throughout

```csharp
// Before — fragile, breaks on spaces in values
_gitExecutor.Execute($"config {key} \"{value}\"");
_gitExecutor.Execute($"tag -a {tagName} -m \"{message}\"");

// After — each argument is a discrete element, no escaping needed
_gitExecutor.Execute(["config", key, value]);
_gitExecutor.Execute(["tag", "-a", tagName, "-m", message]);
```

- **`GitServiceTests`** — mock assertions updated to `A<string[]>.That.Matches(a => a.SequenceEqual(...))`
- **`UpdateCheckerIntegrationTests`** — direct `Execute` call in cleanup updated to array form

